<item>
            <title>[LU-17472] Create programming wrappers (python, go) for liblustreapi Netlink stats API</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17472</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The work of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11850&quot; title=&quot;Relocating /proc/fs/lustre/ost to /sys/kernel/debug/lustre/ost prevents non-root access&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11850&quot;&gt;LU-11850&lt;/a&gt; will restore access of stats to non root users. The limitation to this approach is that external applications that want to harvest stats hate any c coding or linking into libraries. They want use scripts to scrap the data. To address this we can create programming wrappers which external applications can use to collect the stats.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Any environment with python</environment>
